rComments: Great course to bring up your GPA.
Incredibly passionate and insightful. I consulted him about papers on two occasions and he was very helpful and encouraging.
Good Prof- enthusiastic, nice, responds to e-mails promptly. Top notch professor!! You can tell he really loves teaching. Such a good man & incredibly cute too. Hope he doesn't retire any time soon!!
He is a very entertaining professor, really loves what he teaches and makes the material interesting. If you go to the lectures and do the work you can get an A in his course.

I greatly enjoyed his lectures! His random political quips and humour makes for a fun class. Does tend to read off the screen (which ends up being posted online), which can make class boring (sometimes). Textbook also kinda pointless (the one that accompanies the lectures, not the tutorial one).

He definately knows his stuff and is very passionate about teaching it, very helpful to students and extremely well organised.  Formats of tests and assignments are very clear, making it fairly easy to do well.  Absolutely terrific prof, take this course!!
actually the best teacher ever. hes passionate about what he does and it shows. a bit random sometimes during lecture, but whatev the outfit and the accent make up for it. take his classes!!
No Comments

Mason overall is a great professor. It took Greek and Roman Lit & explored it on a different angle which I liked. Lectures were interesting and he is very funny. The class was very light-hearted & very convenient for a busy schedule. The class structure was great!! If you do the readings & show up to class, you will get a good mark. Great class!

He is a great prof.  Probably the best teacher I had in first year.  His lectures were hilarious and very informative.  His gossipy Roman history lectures were especially interesting.  Professor Mason is probably the main reason why I am going to be taking a minor in Classical Civilization.

Mason is clearly one of the most eloquent lecturers at U of T. His lectures are humorous, informative and truely worth attending. Only thing I have against him is that he made Classics look TOO interesting, prompting me to take two vile courses in that program with even more vile instructors.

A wonderful teacher as well as a wonderful person, he gets so excited by what he teaches that it makes you want to learn more. Take his class, give him a hug he is just too cute!
SUCH a good professor. He definitely made coming to class and listening to his lectures worth it, they're amusing and informative. He covers material thoroughly with great enthusiasm.
very cute, entertaining teacher
Very funny and Nice!
Professor Mason definately made me love Greek even more. He was hilarious and helpful. I hope I will be able to have him for a future Greek course.

you know what? even such a great professor like him couldn't help the inherent lameness of cla160. he is a GREAT professor and he loves what he does. the course however was more boring than looking at a cement wall

Wow.  REALLY good prof.  So funny and just all-around interesting to watch!  Good overheads, obviously really loves what he's teaching.  Shame he won't be teaching this course next year - he made the year a lot of fun.

Switched overheads too much, left on maps for forever, and I don't know if it's HIS fault, but the course was not what the description said.. I don't want to know who killed who in what war.  He has good enthusiasm and seems generally nice.
He's a  socking great  prof!  Love the accent, and the political tangents.

He obviously is interested in what he is teaching. He also clearly wants us to learn. He loves his job but sometimes he switches overheads too much. Like your trying to take notes then wham, maps back on for 10 mins while he talks about the notes. hehe
Clear and interested in material.  Wants to help us learn.
Very nice and approachable. He's truly interested in what he teaches.
goes off on too many tangents, boring, way to much information to remember.
